02837nim  2200433Ka ODN0000071105m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130827s2005    nyu     s     000 1 eng d  a9781483050928 (sound recording)  a930F9C3D-1C76-4C2A-B5A2-00F4D8336596bOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aFIC004000aFIC028000aFIC0370002bisacsh1 aOrwell, George.10a1984h[electronic resource].cGeorge Orwell.  aUnabridged.  aAshland :bBlackstone Audio, Inc., and Buck 50 Productions, LLC,c2005.  a1 online resource (11 audio files) :bdigital  a11:23:24  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aUnabridged.0 aNarrator: Simon Prebble.  aBlackstone Audio presents a new recording of this immensely popular book. George Orwell depicts a gray, totalitarian world dominated by Big Brother and its vast network of agents, including the Thought Police, a world in which news is manufactured according to the authorities' will and people live tepid lives by rote. Winston Smith, the hero with no heroic qualities, longs only for truth and decency. But living in a social system in which privacy does not exist and where those with unorthodox ideas are brainwashed or put to death, he knows there is no hope for him. He knows even as he continues to pursue his forbidden love affair that eventually he will come to destruction. The year 1984 has come and gone, yet George Orwell's nightmare vision in 1949 of the world we were becoming is still the great modern classic of negative Utopia. It is a prophetic and haunting tale that exposes the worst crimes imaginable: the destruction of freedom and truth.0 aText Difficulty 9 - Text Difficulty 12  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 320702 KB).17aFiction.2OverDrive 7aClassic Literature.2OverDrive 7aLiterature.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aPrebble, Simon.40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=71105zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=930F9C3D-1C76-4C2A-B5A2-00F4D8336596&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0887-1/%7B930F9C3D-1C76-4C2A-B5A2-00F4D8336596%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0887-1/%7B930F9C3D-1C76-4C2A-B5A2-00F4D8336596%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02542nim  2200409Ka ODN0001435204m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed140731s2013    nyu     s     000 0 eng d  a9781481535281 (sound recording)  a28FEB5BB-A6C0-42DD-A792-05E6E906EEFEbOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aLCO0180002bisacsh1 aLincoln, Abraham.10aAbraham lincoln's second inaugural addressh[electronic resource].cAbraham Lincoln.  aUnabridged.  aAshland :bBlackstone Audio, Inc., and Buck 50 Productions, LLC,c2013.  a1 online resource (1 audio file) :bdigital  a00:05:30  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aUnabridged.0 aNarrator: Dion Graham.  aAbraham Lincoln delivered his second inaugural address on March 4, 1865, during his second inauguration as president of the United States. At a time when victory over the secessionists in the American Civil War was within days and slavery was near an end, Lincoln spoke of sadness. A mere 703 words, Lincoln's speech did not offer the North a victory speech, nor did he excoriate the South for the sin of slavery. Instead, he called on the entire country's guilt for the bloody war and argued for reconciliation and unity. Considered one of his greatest speeches, the address is inscribed, along with the Gettysburg Address, in the Lincoln Memorial.Proceeds from sale of this title go to Reach Out and Read, an innovative literacy advocacy organization.  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 2586 KB).17aNonfiction.2OverDrive 7aHistory.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aGraham, Dion.40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=1435204zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=28FEB5BB-A6C0-42DD-A792-05E6E906EEFE&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0887-1/%7B28FEB5BB-A6C0-42DD-A792-05E6E906EEFE%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0887-1/%7B28FEB5BB-A6C0-42DD-A792-05E6E906EEFE%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02643nim  2200421Ka ODN0000163458m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130827s2008    nyu     s     000 1 eng d  a9781481583077 (sound recording)  a32C806DF-AB04-4F1D-88B1-3199070B2B42bOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aFIC004000aFIC0190002bisacsh1 aPaton, Alan.10aCry, the beloved countryh[electronic resource].cAlan Paton.  aUnabridged.  aAshland :bBlackstone Audio, Inc., and Buck 50 Productions, LLC,c2008.  a1 online resource (9 audio files) :bdigital  a09:48:37  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aUnabridged.0 aNarrator: Michael York.  aA worldwide best-seller when it was first published in 1948, Alan Paton's impassioned novel about a black man's country under white man's law is a work of searing beauty.Cry, the Beloved Country is the deeply moving story of Stephen Kumalo, a Zulu pastor, and his son, Absalom. Set in the troubled and changing South Africa of the 1940s, it is also the story of a land and a people driven by racial injustice. The book is written with such keen compassion and understanding that the listener shares fully in the gravity of the characters' situations.Paton said of his book: "It is a song of love for one's far distant country." Thus, it is a tale that is passionately African while also being timeless and universal. Ultimately, Cry, the Beloved Country is a work of love and hope, of courage and tragedy, born of the dignity of man.0 aText Difficulty 5  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 276328 KB).17aFiction.2OverDrive 7aLiterature.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aYork, Michael.40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=163458zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=32C806DF-AB04-4F1D-88B1-3199070B2B42&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0887-1/%7B32C806DF-AB04-4F1D-88B1-3199070B2B42%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0887-1/%7B32C806DF-AB04-4F1D-88B1-3199070B2B42%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02742nim  2200385Ka ODN0000634326m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130827s2011    nyu     s     000 1 eng d  a9781580818391 (sound recording)  aEE1772DA-E4DF-40A2-8ED8-3F8E465DDF16bOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aFIC0040002bisacsh1 aShakespeare, William.10aMacbethh[electronic resource].cWilliam Shakespeare.  aUnabridged.  a1 online resource (2 audio files) :bdigital  a02:08:28  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aInfamously known as the cursed Scottish play, Macbeth is perhaps Shakespeare's darkest tragedy. When General Macbeth is foretold by three witches that he will one day be King of Scotland, Lady Macbeth convinces him to get rid of anyone who could stand in his way &amp;#8211; including committing regicide. As Macbeth ascends to the throne through bloody murder, he becomes a tyrant consumed by fear and paranoia.An L.A. Theatre Works full-cast performance featuring:James Marsters as Macbeth;Joanne Whalley as Lady Macbeth;Josh Cooke as Banquo and others;JD Cullum as Macduff and Second Murderer;Dan Donohue as Ross;Jeannie Elias as Second Witch and others;Chuma Gault as Lennox and Servant;Jon Matthews as Malcolm;Alan Shearman as Angus and others;Andr&#233; Sogliuzzo as Donalbain, Third Witch and others;Kate Steele as Lady Macduff, First Witch and Apparition;Kris Tabori as Duncan and others.Directed by Martin Jarvis. Sound effects by Tony Palermo. Recorded at the Invisible Studios, West Hollywood in May, 2011.  aElectronic reproduction.bVenice :cL.A. Theatre Works,d2011.nRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 120517 KB).17aFiction.2OverDrive 7aClassic Literature.2OverDrive 7aDrama.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 cOriginalz978158081838440uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=634326zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=EE1772DA-E4DF-40A2-8ED8-3F8E465DDF16&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/1095-1/%7BEE1772DA-E4DF-40A2-8ED8-3F8E465DDF16%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/1095-1/%7BEE1772DA-E4DF-40A2-8ED8-3F8E465DDF16%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02625nim  2200409Ka ODN0000257052m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130829s2009    nyu     s     000 1 eng d  a9781580816908 (sound recording)  aDA43BEB0-6160-4067-96E8-4289AC48F75BbOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aDRA0000002bisacsh1 aSteinbeck, John.14aThe grapes of wrathh[electronic resource].cJohn Steinbeck.  aAbridged.  aVenice :bL.A. Theatre Works,c2009.  a1 online resource (2 audio files) :bdigital  a01:58:55  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aAbridged.  aBased on the epic novel by Nobel Laureate John Steinbeck. Set during the Great Depression, The Grapes of Wrath tells the powerful story of the Joad family's trek from the dust bowl of Oklahoma to the promise of a new life in California. But what they find threatens to rip apart their lives, and sever the ties that bind them together. Starring Shirley Knight as Ma Joad, Frank Galati's heart-wrenching adaptation of the Pulitzer Prize-winning novel finds its timeless heart in the generous spirit of the common man.A full-cast production featuring: Shirley Knight, Jeffrey Donovan, Emily Bergl, Mike Buie, Daniel Chacon, Maurice Chasse, Shannon Cochran, Trista Delamere, Francis Guinan, Charlie Matthes, Rod McLachlan, Bob Pescovitz,Joel Rafael, Stephen Ramsey, Nick Sadler, Andy Taylor, Todd Waring, Fredd Wayne, Michael Weston and Kate Williamson with live music performed by the Joel Rafael Band.0 aText Difficulty 3  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 55849 KB).17aFiction.2OverDrive 7aDrama.2OverDrive 7aLiterature.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=257052zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=DA43BEB0-6160-4067-96E8-4289AC48F75B&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/1095-1/%7BDA43BEB0-6160-4067-96E8-4289AC48F75B%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/1095-1/%7BDA43BEB0-6160-4067-96E8-4289AC48F75B%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image03024nim  2200421Ka ODN0000132037m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130827s2007    nyu     s     000 1 eng d  a9781481540544 (sound recording)  a61963FAD-1F22-442B-9B80-4FEB16F602F8bOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aFIC004000aFIC019000aFIC0370002bisacsh1 aOrwell, George.10aAnimal farmh[electronic resource].cGeorge Orwell.  aUnabridged.  aAshland :bBlackstone Audio, Inc., and Buck 50 Productions, LLC,c2007.  a1 online resource (3 audio files) :bdigital  a03:11:47  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aUnabridged.0 aNarrator: Ralph Cosham.  aGeorge Orwell's classic satire of the Russian Revolution has become an intimate part of our contemporary culture, with its treatment of democratic, fascist, and socialist ideals through an animal fable. The animals of Mr. Jones' Manor Farm are overworked, mistreated, and desperately seeking a reprieve. In their quest to create an idyllic society where justice and equality reign, the animals of Manor Farm revolt against their human rulers, establishing the democratic Animal Farm under the credo, "All Animals Are Created Equal." Out of their cleverness, the pigs&amp;#8212;Napoleon, Squealer, and Snowball&amp;#8212;emerge as leaders of the new community. In a development of insidious familiarity, the pigs begin to assume ever greater amounts of power, while other animals, especially the faithful horse Boxer, assume more of the work. The climax of the story is the brutal betrayal of Boxer, when totalitarian rule is reestablished with the bloodstained postscript to the founding slogan: "But Some Animals Are More Equal than Others." This astonishing allegory, one of the most scathing satires in literary history, remains as fresh and relevant as the day it was published.0 aText Difficulty 9 - Text Difficulty 12  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 90033 KB).17aFiction.2OverDrive 7aClassic Literature.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aCosham, Ralph.40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=132037zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=61963FAD-1F22-442B-9B80-4FEB16F602F8&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0887-1/%7B61963FAD-1F22-442B-9B80-4FEB16F602F8%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0887-1/%7B61963FAD-1F22-442B-9B80-4FEB16F602F8%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02228nim  2200445Ka ODN0000076627m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130920s2005    nyu    js     000 1 eng d  a9780060835026 (sound recording)  aE2AE26F0-FCA7-4E30-AB35-55A5D42B0D6AbOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aJUV000000aJUV006000aJUV0190002bisacsh1 aGutman, Dan.14aThe get rich quick clubh[electronic resource].cDan Gutman.  aUnabridged.  a1 online resource (2 audio files) :bdigital  a01:58:55  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda0 aNarrator: Angela Goethals.  aWe, the members of the Get Rich Quick Club, in order to form a more perfect summer, vow we will figure out a way to make a million dollars by September. We agree that neither rain nor snow nor gloom of night will prevent us from achieving our stated goal, until death do us part.0 aText Difficulty 2 - Text Difficulty 32 aMG/Middle grades (4th-8th)8 a640bLexile.8 a4.1bATOS Level  aElectronic reproduction.bNew York :cHarperAudio,d2005.nRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 55834 KB).17aJuvenile Fiction.2OverDrive 7aJuvenile Literature.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aGoethals, Angela.1 cOriginalz978006073586940uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=76627zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=E2AE26F0-FCA7-4E30-AB35-55A5D42B0D6A&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0293-1/%7BE2AE26F0-FCA7-4E30-AB35-55A5D42B0D6A%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0293-1/%7BE2AE26F0-FCA7-4E30-AB35-55A5D42B0D6A%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02473nim  2200409Ka ODN0000715837m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130827s2012    nyu     s     000 1 eng d  a9781580818797 (sound recording)  a41EAD618-6BE5-4935-9791-5F4705C3275CbOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aFIC0040002bisacsh1 aIbsen, Henrik.12aA doll's househ[electronic resource].cHenrik Ibsen.  aUnabridged.  aVenice :bL.A. Theatre Works,c2012.  a1 online resource (2 audio files) :bdigital  a02:10:27  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aUnabridged.  aNora Helmer has everything a young housewife could want: beautiful children, an adoring husband, and a bright future. But when a carelessly buried secret rises from the past, Nora's well-calibrated domestic ideal starts to crumble. Ibsen's play is as fresh today as it was when it first stormed the stages of 19th-century Europe.An L.A. Theatre Works full-cast performance featuring:Calista Flockhart as Nora HelmerTony Abatemarco as Dr. RankTim Dekay as Torvald HelmerJeannie Elias as Anne-Marie/ HeleneGregory Itzin as Nils KrogstadJobeth Williams as Mrs. LindeTranslated by Rolf Fjelde. Directed by Rosalind Ayres. Recorded before a live audience at the James Bridges Theater at UCLA School of Theater, Film and Television in September, 2011.0 aText Difficulty 4  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 61268 KB).17aFiction.2OverDrive 7aClassic Literature.2OverDrive 7aDrama.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=715837zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=41EAD618-6BE5-4935-9791-5F4705C3275C&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/1095-1/%7B41EAD618-6BE5-4935-9791-5F4705C3275C%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/1095-1/%7B41EAD618-6BE5-4935-9791-5F4705C3275C%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02594nim  2200433Ka ODN0000142866m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130827s2007    nyu     s     000 1 eng d  a9781483071015 (sound recording)  a1A165B96-E154-4716-8781-8008B9C97C89bOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aFIC000000aFIC004000aFIC0190002bisacsh1 aBuck, Pearl S.14aThe good earthh[electronic resource] :bHouse of Earth Trilogy, Book 1.cPearl S Buck.  aUnabridged.  aAshland :bBlackstone Audio, Inc., and Buck 50 Productions, LLC,c2007.  a1 online resource (9 audio files) :bdigital  a10:37:56  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda0 aHouse of Earth Trilogy.  aUnabridged.0 aNarrator: Anthony Heald.  aThis Pulitzer Prize-winning classic tells the poignant tale of a Chinese farmer and his family in old agrarian China. The humble Wang Lung glories in the soil he works, nurturing the land as it nurtures him and his family. Nearby, the nobles of the House of Hwang consider themselves above the land and its workers; but they will soon meet their own downfall.Hard times come upon Wang Lung and his family when flood and drought force them to seek work in the city. The working people riot, breaking into the homes of the rich and forcing them to flee. When Wang Lung shows mercy to one noble and is rewarded, he begins to rise in the world, even as the House of Hwang falls.0 aText Difficulty 9 - Text Difficulty 12  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 299440 KB).17aFiction.2OverDrive 7aClassic Literature.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aHeald, Anthony.40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=142866zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=1A165B96-E154-4716-8781-8008B9C97C89&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0887-1/%7B1A165B96-E154-4716-8781-8008B9C97C89%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0887-1/%7B1A165B96-E154-4716-8781-8008B9C97C89%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02900nim  2200433Ka ODN0000076192m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130827s2004    nyu    js     000 1 eng d  a9780060817961 (sound recording)  a11535BB5-7F33-4E59-85FF-97967A476E3DbOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aJUV002120aJUV019000aJUV0430002bisacsh1 aLobel, Arnold.10aFrog and toad audio collectionh[electronic resource].cArnold Lobel.  aUnabridged.  a1 online resource (2 audio files) :bdigital  a01:30:49  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda0 aI Can Read Book.0 aNarrator: Arnold Lobel.  aCelebrate the power of friendship with all four of the beloved Frog and Toad I Can Read stories by Arnold LobelThis audio collections includes all four classics: Frog and Toad Are Friends, Frog and Toad Together, Frog and Toad All Year, and Days with Frog and Toad. Share the adventures of best friends Frog and Toad as they fly a kite, resist the temptation of cookies, and search for a lost button. No matter what kind of situation they find themselves in, one thing is certain: Frog and Toad will always be together. This reading collection is a Level Two I Can Read, geared toward kids who read on their own but still need a little help. The classic Frog and Toad stories by Arnold Lobel have won numerous awards and honors, including a Newbery Honor (Frog and Toad Together), a Caldecott Honor (Frog and Toad Are Friends), ALA Notable Children's Book, Fanfare Honor List (The Horn Book), School Library Journal Best Children's Book, and Library of Congress Children's Book.0 aText Difficulty K - Text Difficulty 2  aElectronic reproduction.bNew York :cHarperAudio,d2004.nRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 42676 KB).17aJuvenile Fiction.2OverDrive 7aBeginning Reader.2OverDrive 7aShort Stories.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aLobel, Arnold.1 cOriginalz978006058445040uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=76192zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=11535BB5-7F33-4E59-85FF-97967A476E3D&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0293-1/%7B11535BB5-7F33-4E59-85FF-97967A476E3D%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0293-1/%7B11535BB5-7F33-4E59-85FF-97967A476E3D%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02567nim  2200433Ka ODN0000470761m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed131211s2010    nyu    js     000 1 eng d  a9780061768194 (sound recording)  aABD96F74-5F64-4C8C-903D-B8022998C6B4bOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aJUV002070aJUV005000aJUV0190002bisacsh1 aCleary, Beverly.10aHenry and beezush[electronic resource] :bHenry Huggins Series, Book 2.cBeverly Cleary.  aUnabridged.  a1 online resource (3 audio files) :bdigital  a02:31:22  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda0 aHenry Huggins.0 aNarrator: William Roberts.  aNewbery Medal&amp;#8211;winner Beverly Cleary tells the story of a boy with a goal&amp;#8212;and the girl who helps him achieve it. Well-meaning Henry Huggins would do anything to get the bike of his dreams. But every idea he has keeps falling flat. Selling bubble gum on the playground gets him in trouble with his teacher. There's the paper route, but Henry's dog Ribsy nearly ruins that with his nose for mischief. Even pesky little Ramona Quimby manages to get in the way of Henry's chance at a bike. But it's with the help of his best friend Beezus that there may be a way. After all&amp;#8212;with a friend by your side, anything is possible.0 aText Difficulty 38 a730bLexile.  aElectronic reproduction.bNew York :cHarperAudio,d2010.nRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 70968 KB).17aJuvenile Fiction.2OverDrive 7aJuvenile Literature.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aRoberts, William.1 cOriginalz978006051049740uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=470761zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=ABD96F74-5F64-4C8C-903D-B8022998C6B4&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0293-1/%7BABD96F74-5F64-4C8C-903D-B8022998C6B4%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0293-1/%7BABD96F74-5F64-4C8C-903D-B8022998C6B4%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02801nim  2200397Ka ODN0000798942m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130923s2012    nyu     s     000 1 eng d  a9781580818810 (sound recording)  a8BF51CB6-247E-44E1-8FDD-B9229897A83CbOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aDRA0000002bisacsh1 aShakespeare, William.10aHamleth[electronic resource].cWilliam Shakespeare.  aUnabridged.  aVenice :bL.A. Theatre Works,c2012.  a1 online resource (3 audio files) :bdigital  a03:13:50  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aUnabridged.  aShakespeare's timeless story of revenge, corruption, and murder is considered one of the greatest works in the English language. Prince Hamlet sets out to avenge his beloved father's death at the hand of his uncle Claudius &#8212; but Hamlet's spiral into grief and madness will have permanent and immutable consequences for the Kingdom of Denmark. Composed over 400 years ago, Hamlet remains one of the theater's most studied and performed works, and is presented here in a stunning, sound-rich full-cast recording.An L.A. Theatre Works full-cast performance featuring:Josh Stamberg as HamletStephen Collins as King ClaudiusJoBeth Williams as Queen GertrudeStacy Keach as GhostAlan Mandell as PoloniusEmily Swallow as OpheliaJD Cullum as LaertesMatthew Wolf as HoratioMark Capri as Ambassador and othersJosh Clark as Gravedigger, Voltemand and othersHenri Lubatti as Rosencrantz and othersJon Matthews as Guildenstern and othersDarren Richardson as Player Queen and othersAndr&#233; Sogliuzzo as Reynaldo and othersDirected by Martin Jarvis. Recorded at the Invisible Studios, West Hollywood in August, 2011.  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 90969 KB).17aFiction.2OverDrive 7aDrama.2OverDrive 7aLiterature.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=798942zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=8BF51CB6-247E-44E1-8FDD-B9229897A83C&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/1095-1/%7B8BF51CB6-247E-44E1-8FDD-B9229897A83C%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/1095-1/%7B8BF51CB6-247E-44E1-8FDD-B9229897A83C%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02884nim  2200457Ka ODN0000166796m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130829s2008    nyu    js     000 1 eng d  a9780061712180 (sound recording)  aB3060579-817D-4B9A-990E-BD386E083480bOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aJUV002120aJUV039050aJUV0390602bisacsh1 aLobel, Arnold.10aFrog and toad togetherh[electronic resource].cArnold Lobel.  aUnabridged.  a1 online resource (1 audio file) :bdigital  a00:23:33  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda0 aI Can Read Book.0 aNarrator: Arnold Lobel.  aThe beloved classic about friendship&amp;#8212;a Newbery Honor Book!Frog and Toad are best friends&amp;#8212;they do everything together. When Toad admires the flowers in Frog's garden, Frog gives him seeds to grow a garden of his own. When Toad bakes cookies, Frog helps him eat them. And when both Frog and Toad are scared, they are brave together. School Library Journal called this story collection from Arnold Lobel "a masterpiece of child-styled humor and sensitivity."Winner of the Newbery Honor award, Frog and Toad Together is a Level Two I Can Read book, geared for kids who read on their own but still need a little help.The classic Frog and Toad stories by Arnold Lobel have won numerous awards and honors, including a Newbery Honor, a Caldecott Honor, ALA Notable Children's Book, Fanfare Honor List (Horn Book), School Library Journal Best Children's Book, and Library of Congress Children's Book.0 aText Difficulty 1 - Text Difficulty 22 aLG/Lower grades (K-3rd)8 a450bLexile.8 a2.9bATOS Level  aElectronic reproduction.bNew York :cHarperAudio,d2008.nRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 11049 KB).17aJuvenile Fiction.2OverDrive 7aBeginning Reader.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aLobel, Arnold.1 cOriginalz978006023959640uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=166796zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=B3060579-817D-4B9A-990E-BD386E083480&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0293-1/%7BB3060579-817D-4B9A-990E-BD386E083480%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0293-1/%7BB3060579-817D-4B9A-990E-BD386E083480%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image02440nim  2200445Ka ODN0000077005m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130827s2005    nyu    js     000 1 eng d  a9780060854423 (sound recording)  a9BF20BC6-2808-492B-AB70-D512EC79308BbOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aJUV001000aJUV007000aJUV0370002bisacsh1 aLewis, C. S.10aPrince caspianh[electronic resource] :bThe Chronicles of Narnia, Book 4.cC. S Lewis.  aUnabridged.  a1 online resource (4 audio files) :bdigital  a04:41:07  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda0 aThe Chronicles of Narnia.0 aNarrator: Lynn Redgrave.  aNarnia ... the land between the lamp-post and the Castle of Cair Paravel, where animals talk, where magical things happen ... and where the adventure begins.Peter, Susan, Edmund, and Lucy are returning to boarding school when they are summoned from the dreary train station (by Susan's own magic horn) to return to the land of Narnia &amp;#8212; the land where they had ruled as kings and queens and where their help is desperately needed.Performed by Lynn Redgrave0 aText Difficulty 7 - Text Difficulty 122 aMG/Middle grades (4th-8th)8 a5.7bATOS Level  aElectronic reproduction.bNew York :cHarperAudio,d2005.nRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 131786 KB).17aJuvenile Fiction.2OverDrive 7aFantasy.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aRedgrave, Lynn.1 cOriginalz978006056439140uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=77005zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=9BF20BC6-2808-492B-AB70-D512EC79308B&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0293-1/%7B9BF20BC6-2808-492B-AB70-D512EC79308B%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0293-1/%7B9BF20BC6-2808-492B-AB70-D512EC79308B%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image03548nim  2200409Ka ODN0000351223m        h        cr una---     sz usn nn   ed130924s2010    nyu     s     000 0 eng d  a9781481587112 (sound recording)  a3FCAF3C4-FAEB-41AD-878B-DAD6EF2835CFbOverDrive, Inc.nhttp://www.overdrive.com  aTEFODcTEFOD  aBIO0060002bisacsh1 aUnger, Harlow Giles.10aLion of libertyh[electronic resource] :bPatrick Henry and the Call to a New Nation.cHarlow Giles Unger.  aUnabridged.  aAshland :bBlackstone Audio, Inc., and Buck 50 Productions, LLC,c2010.  a1 online resource (9 audio files) :bdigital  a09:30:08  aspoken wordbspw2rdacontent  aaudiobs2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aaudio file2rda  aUnabridged.0 aNarrator: William Hughes.  aKnown to generations of Americans for his stirring call to arms, "Give me liberty or give me death," Patrick Henry is all but forgotten today as the first of the Founding Fathers to call for independence, the first to call for revolution, and the first to call for a bill of rights. If Washington was the "Sword of the Revolution" and Jefferson, "the Pen," Patrick Henry more than earned his epithet as "the Trumpet" of the Revolution for rousing Americans to arms in the Revolutionary War. Henry was one of the towering figures of the nation's formative years and perhaps the greatest orator in American history. To this day, many Americans misunderstand what Patrick Henry's cry for "liberty or death" meant to him and to his tens of thousands of devoted followers in Virginia. A prototype of the eighteenth- and nineteenth-century American frontiersman, Henry claimed individual liberties as a "natural right" to live free of "the tyranny of rulers"&amp;#8212;American as well as British. Henry believed that individual rights were more secure in small republics than in large republics, which many of the other Founding Fathers hoped to create after the Revolution. Henry was one of the most important and colorful of our Founding Fathers&amp;#8212;a driving force behind three of the most important events in American history: the War of Independence, the enactment of the Bill of Rights, and, tragically, as America's first important proponent of state's rights, the Civil War. This biography is history at its best, telling a story both human and philosophical. As Unger points out, Henry's words continue to echo across America and inspire millions to fight government intrusion in their daily lives.  aRequires OverDrive Listen (file size: N/A KB) or OverDrive app (file size: 267659 KB).17aNonfiction.2OverDrive 7aBiography & Autobiography.2OverDrive 7aElectronic books.2local1 aHughes, William.40uhttp://link.overdrive.com/?websiteID=173&titleID=351223zClick to access digital title.4 3Excerptuhttps://samples.overdrive.com/?crid=3FCAF3C4-FAEB-41AD-878B-DAD6EF2835CF&.epub-sample.overdrive.comzSample4 3Imageuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-100/0887-1/%7B3FCAF3C4-FAEB-41AD-878B-DAD6EF2835CF%7DImg100.jpgzLarge cover image4 3Thumbnailuhttps://img1.od-cdn.com/ImageType-200/0887-1/%7B3FCAF3C4-FAEB-41AD-878B-DAD6EF2835CF%7DImg200.jpgzThumbnail cover image